snippet.title: NEW! Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah - Ep 3697 - 17 Feb 2023 - Teaser
snippet.description:
Episode 3697: The Prankster Returns
--------------------------------------------------------
Tapu makes a grand entry that surprises everyone. Jetha and Bapuji get really happy after seeing Tapu. Bhide gets a little irritated because of Tapu's mysterious, quirky gifts. Even Iyer complains about the strange robot that he received. Anyway, Tapu Sena celebrates Tapu's entry with a group dance. Sonu, Gogi, and Hans all shake their legs with Tapu and feel extreme joy at their friend's return. Stay tuned to witness more fun and frolic!

Show Name ‚Äì Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah
Star Cast ‚Äì  Dilip Joshi, Disha Vakani, Amit Bhatt, Nitish Bhaluni
Episodes No - 3697, 17 Feb 2023
Produced By - Asit Kumar Modi

#TaarakMehtaKaOoltahChashmah #‡§§‡§æ‡§∞‡§ï‡§Æ‡•á‡§π‡§§‡§æ‡§ï‡§æ‡§â‡§≤‡•ç‡§ü‡§æ‡§ö‡§∂‡•ç‡§Æ‡§æ #sab 

Click here to subscribe to SAB TV:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC6-F5tO8uklgE9Zy8IvbdFw?sub_confirmation=1

Click here to subscribe to SonyLIV: 
http://www.sonyliv.com/signin

About The Show
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in Gokuldham Co-operative Society and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. Jethalal lives in Gokuldham society and owns an electronics shop.  'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Nitish Bhaluni). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises.

Click here to watch the episode of Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah :

Meerab is an ambitious and beautiful young girl who wants to pursue higher studies. Her entire world revolves around her parents and she believes in them the most. Her strong and confident personality makes her stand against social injustices around her.

On the contrary, Murtasim hails from a powerful and influential family. He respects and values the morals and traditions of his family and refuses to let the family down.

Meerab‚Äôs life takes an unexpected turn when she finds out about her family‚Äôs decision regarding her and Murtasim‚Äôs life. Meerab‚Äôs hatred towards Murtasim continues to grow as a family secret from the past resurfaces. Coming from different backgrounds and mindsets, Murtasim begins to realize Meerab‚Äôs arrogant behaviour towards him and begins to consider her a challenge for himself. On the other hand, Meerab who is used to living her life on her own terms refuses to accept Murtasim‚Äôs family traditions and unnecessary social barriers.

Soon their lives go through a series of emotional sufferings and misunderstandings where it becomes difficult for them to coexist. Despite their hatred towards each other, will Meerab and Murtasim accept their true feelings or will the dynamics of ego and self-respect force them to stay apart?

Method (Sabudana vada) ‚Äì
‚Ä¢ Wash the sabudana well, drain the water then add 2-3 tbsp water and cover and soak it for 5-6 hours.
‚Ä¢ After 5-6 hours take soaked sago into a parat / big plate.
‚Ä¢ Grind sabudana on pulse mode for a sec only .
‚Ä¢ Add sabudana into parat or plate and add boiled potatoes and mash and mix well.
‚Ä¢ Then add salt, sugar, red chilly pw, green chilly, crushed peanut pw , cumin, fresh coriander and mix well. 
‚Ä¢ Then make flat vadas and deep fry into medium hot oil. 
‚Ä¢ Super Crispy Sabudana vada is ready to serve with chutley.

India is the largest democracy in the world. The right to vote and more
importantly the exercise of franchise by the eligible citizens is at the heart of

development and benefit of all the citizens.

Haan haan maalum
Hai hume bahut late ho gaya aane mein
Pure 10 nahi nahi 11 mahine lag gaye hume
Lekin tum log ko kya batau aisi fatti padi thi hum log ka kuch aisa project tha jisse plan karte karte karte 6-7 mahine aise nikle hume pata hi nai chala
Fir humne ye saal ka bigg boss dekha aur decide kiya abhi toh hum season 2 banaenge hi kaise bhi
Wo jo project hai jiski baat kar raha hu abhi back burner pe hai but promise hai hum usse kaise bhi aapke saamne laaengeüòç

Abhi subah ke 6 baje main ye description bathroom mein likh raha hu seth log toh please deri ke lie maaf kar do baaki tum log hi seth ho mere dhani ho muje maalum hai naraazgi hogi lekin utna hi pyaar bhi karte ho
Chalo abhi video ka Favourite part comment karo aur apna fav dialogue bhi likh lo

Chalo abhi production ka batao is video ka

Actors : wahi sasti team jisme dusre actors ki kami hoti, Akash Dodeja aka jadoo aka gareeb Kunal Chhabhria aka is baar wo kisi ke baap nahi gaya Vibhu Varshney humare video ke super star Simran Dhanwani rotlu pitbul Rohit Sadhwani belt waala anti-singham Tanish Sirwani sandaswala Grishim Nawani dubai waala Akash Jagtap thapad khaane waala Paras rupani playground ka rejected player, Ritesh Sadhwani bhi tha video mein bas ek scene mein kyunki saala gumm ho gaya tha Shivkumar Parthasarathy as humare big-bull Vivek Menon humare super super star as humare host
And ajay bhai jinhone teddy bear ka body double play kiya

'Vande Guru Paramparaam' - spiritual musical series produced by Sri Kuldeep M Pai is a genuine attempt at infusing the abundance of our cultural heritage in the younger generations. What better agency than Music can there be to inspire the young and aged alike? A team of talented kids spearheaded by Sooryagayathri, Rahul Vellal, Bhavya Ganapathi, Raghuram Manikandan and Paavani Cotah have played their parts in transferring the Transcendental Truth through their dulcet voices. The musical videos in this series have already won acclaim from millions of viewers across the globe. It's now time for us to bow before the lineage of Gurus and relish the beatitude of divine buoyancy. Vande Guru Paramparaam! Vande Guru Paramparaam!

snippet.title: Sabudana Khichdi Recipe | ‡§∏‡§æ‡§¨‡•Ç‡§¶‡§æ‡§®‡§æ ‡§ñ‡§ø‡§ö‡§°‡§º‡•Ä ‡§¨‡§®‡§æ‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§Ü‡§∏‡§æ‡§® ‡§§‡§∞‡•Ä‡§ï‡§æ | Chef Sanjyot Keer
snippet.description:
Full written recipe for Sabudana Khichdi

Prep time: 10 minutes (excluding soaking time)
Cooking time: 10-15 minutes
Serves: 3-4 people

Ingredients:
SABUDANA | ‡§∏‡§æ‡§¨‡•Ç‡§¶‡§æ‡§®‡§æ 1.5 CUPS
WATER | ‡§™‡§æ‡§®‡•Ä 1.5 CUPS
PEANUTS | ‡§Æ‡•Ç‡§Ç‡§ó‡§´‡§≤‡•Ä 1/2 CUP
GHEE | ‡§ò‡•Ä 2 TBSP
CUMIN SEEDS | ‡§ú‡•Ä‡§∞‡§æ 2 TSP
GREEN CHILLI | ‡§π‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö 2-3 (CHOPPED)
CURRY LEAVES | ‡§ï‡§°‡§º‡•Ä ‡§™‡§§‡•ç‡§§‡•á 10-12 NOS. 
POTATO | ‡§Ü‡§≤‡•Ç 2 NOS. (BOILED & DICED)
SALT | ‡§®‡§Æ‡§ï TO TASTE
SUGAR | ‡§∂‡§ï‡•ç‡§ï‡§∞ 1/2 TSP
LEMON JUICE | ‡§®‡§ø‡§Ç‡§¨‡•Ç ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§∞‡§∏ OF 0.5-1 LEMON
FRESH CORIANDER | ‡§π‡§∞‡§æ ‡§ß‡§®‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ A HANDFUL (CHOPPED)
Method:
Add the sabudana in a sieve & wash them using water, then transfer the washed sabudana in a large bowl & add equal amount of water, cover & let them soak for 4-5 hours until all the water has been soaked up.
Add the peanuts into a mortar or a chopper & grind it coarsely, you don‚Äôt have to make a powder.
Set a kadhai over high flame & once it gets hot, add ghee & once the ghee gets hot, add cumin seeds, green chilli, curry leaves & potatoes, stir & cook for 1-2 minutes.
Further add the crushed peanuts along with soaked sabudana, salt, sugar & lemon juice, stir well & then lower the flame, cover the kadhai with a lid & let it cook for 3-4 minutes, or until the sabudana turns translucent.
Lastly, sprinkle some fresh coriander & stir.
Your sabudana khichdi is ready.

Meerab is an ambitious and beautiful young girl who wants to pursue higher studies. Her entire world revolves around her parents and she believes in them the most. Her strong and confident personality makes her stand against social injustices around her.

On the contrary, Murtasim hails from a powerful and influential family. He respects and values the morals and traditions of his family and refuses to let the family down.

Meerab‚Äôs life takes an unexpected turn when she finds out about her family‚Äôs decision regarding her and Murtasim‚Äôs life. Meerab‚Äôs hatred towards Murtasim continues to grow as a family secret from the past resurfaces. Coming from different backgrounds and mindsets, Murtasim begins to realize Meerab‚Äôs arrogant behaviour towards him and begins to consider her a challenge for himself. On the other hand, Meerab who is used to living her life on her own terms refuses to accept Murtasim‚Äôs family traditions and unnecessary social barriers.

Soon their lives go through a series of emotional sufferings and misunderstandings where it becomes difficult for them to coexist. Despite their hatred towards each other, will Meerab and Murtasim accept their true feelings or will the dynamics of ego and self-respect force them to stay apart?

The first thrilling investigative series on Indian Television is today one of the most popular shows on Sony Entertainment Television. The series consists of hard-core police procedural stories dealing with investigation, detection, and suspense. The protagonists of the serial are an elite group of police officers belonging to the Crime Investigation Department of the police force, led by ACP Pradyuman [played by the dynamic Shivaji Satam]. We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Shailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi / Raj Anadkat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

‡§â‡§™‡§µ‡§æ‡§∏‡§∏‡§æ‡§†‡•Ä ‡§∞‡§§‡§æ‡§≥‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§ö‡•á ‡§ò‡§æ‡§∞‡§ó‡•á | Sweet potato Puri for Fasting  ‚Äì 
‡§∏‡§æ‡§π‡§ø‡§§‡•ç‡§Ø | Ingredients 
‚Ä¢ ‡§∞‡§§‡§æ‡§≥‡•á 250 ‡§ó‡•ç‡§∞‡§æ‡§Æ‡•ç‡§∏ | Sweet Potato 250 grams 
‚Ä¢ ‡§ï‡§ø‡§∏‡§≤‡•á‡§≤‡§æ ‡§ó‡•Ç‡§≥ ¬Ω ‡§ï‡§™ | Chopped Jaggery ¬Ω Cup
‚Ä¢ ‡§Æ‡•Ä‡§† ‡§ö‡§µ‡•Ä‡§®‡•Å‡§∏‡§æ‡§∞ | Salt to taste
‚Ä¢ ‡§µ‡§∞‡§à ‡§™‡•Ä‡§† 1 ‡§§‡•á ‡§∏‡§µ‡§æ ‡§ï‡§™ ‡§Ö‡§Ç‡§¶‡§æ‡§ú‡•á | Sama Flour 1-1 ¬º Cup Approx
‚Ä¢ ‡§§‡§≥‡§£‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§∏‡§æ‡§†‡•Ä ‡§§‡•á‡§≤ | Oil for frying
Method ‚Äì 
‚Ä¢ Wash sweet potatoes well, keep it in a pressure cooker tin, put some water at the bottom of the pressure cooker, put sweet potato tin into the pressure cooker, and take 2 whistles. 
‚Ä¢ Let the pressure release from pressure cooker, take potato out and let it cool down completely. 
‚Ä¢ Once cool down, peel the skin from potato and grate the potato.
‚Ä¢ Add grated jaggery and salt to taste and mix well.
‚Ä¢ Then add sama flour to make semi soft dough, cover the dough and let it rest for 10 mintues,
‚Ä¢ After mins, take small lemon sized ball from the dough.
‚Ä¢ On rolling pad put butter paper, apply some ghee onto it , put ball onto it again put butter paper on the top of the dough and gently press the dough with the help of a plate. 
‚Ä¢ Puri is ready, deep fry puri on med to high heat. 

Sabudana Khichadi Recipe | ‡§∏‡§æ‡§¨‡•Å‡§¶‡§æ‡§£‡§æ ‡§ñ‡§ø‡§ö‡§°‡•Ä ‡§∞‡•á‡§∏‡§ø‡§™‡•Ä 
‚Ä¢ ‡§∏‡§æ‡§¨‡•Ç‡§¶‡§æ‡§£‡§æ 1 ‡§ï‡§™ | Sago 1 Cup 
‚Ä¢ ‡§∏‡§æ‡§ú‡•Ç‡§ï ‡§§‡•Ç‡§™ 3 ‡§ö‡§Æ‡§ö‡•á | Ghee 2-3 tbsp
‚Ä¢ ‡§¨‡§ü‡§æ‡§ü‡§æ 1 ‡§Æ‡§ß‡•ç‡§Ø‡§Æ | Potato 1 med
‚Ä¢ ‡§π‡§ø‡§∞‡§µ‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡§ö‡•Ä ‡§§‡•Å‡§ï‡§°‡•á 1 tbsp | Green chillies chopped 1 tbsp
‚Ä¢ ‡§∏‡§æ‡§ñ‡§∞ 1 ‡§ö‡§Æ‡§ö‡§æ | Sugar 1 tsp
‚Ä¢ ‡§∏‡•à‡§Ç‡§ß‡§µ ‡§Æ‡•Ä‡§† ‡§ö‡§µ‡•Ä‡§®‡•Å‡§∏‡§æ‡§∞ | Pink Himalayan Salt to taste
‚Ä¢ ‡§≠‡§æ‡§ú‡§≤‡•á‡§≤‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§¶‡§æ‡§£‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§ö‡§æ ‡§ú‡§æ‡§°‡§∏‡§∞ ‡§ï‡•Ç‡§ü 3/4 ‡§ï‡§™ | Raosted peanuts crushed ¬æ cup
‚Ä¢ ‡§¶‡•Ç‡§ß 2-3 tbsp | Milk 2-3 tbsp
Method ‚Äì
‚Ä¢ Wash the sago well, keep some water into it and soak it overnight or for about 5-6 hours. (you add some milk while soaking the sago) 
‚Ä¢ Heat up some oil / ghee into a kadhai add green chilies and potatoes and some salt and saute on med heat till potatoes get nice golden brown color 
‚Ä¢ Then add sugar, roasted peanut crushed and saute for a min on low heat.
‚Ä¢ Then add soaked sago and salt to taste and saute on med heat for about 3-4 minutes, then cover and cook on low heat for 2 minutes.
‚Ä¢ After 2 minutes add milk and again stir for abut 2 minutes and again cover and cook for a min on low heat. 
‚Ä¢ After a min check again, stir for a min and serve hot. 

 ‡§®‡§æ‡§∞‡§≥‡§æ‡§ö‡•Ä ‡§ñ‡•Ä‡§∞ ‡§∞‡•á‡§∏‡§ø‡§™‡•Ä | Coconut Kheer Recipe 
‚Ä¢ ‡§ì‡§≤‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§®‡§æ‡§∞‡§≥‡§æ‡§ö‡§æ ‡§ö‡§µ 1 ‡§ï‡§™ | Fresh coconut scraped 1 Cup
‚Ä¢ ‡§¶‡•Ç‡§ß ‡§Ö‡§∞‡•ç‡§ß‡§æ ‡§≤‡§ø‡§ü‡§∞ | Milk ¬Ω Liter 
‚Ä¢ ‡§∏‡§æ‡§ñ‡§∞ ¬Ω ‡§ï‡§™ | Sugar ¬Ω Cup
‚Ä¢ ‡§ï‡§æ‡§ú‡•Ç , ‡§¨‡§¶‡§æ‡§Æ ‡§™‡§ø‡§∏‡•ç‡§§‡§æ ‡§ï‡§æ‡§™ | Cashew, Almond pista 
‚Ä¢ ‡§∏‡§æ‡§ú‡•Ç‡§ï ‡§§‡•Ç‡§™ 1 ‡§ö‡§Æ‡§ö‡§æ | Ghee 1 tsp
Method ‚Äì
‚Ä¢ Heat some ghee into a kadhai and add scraped coconut and roast for 2-3 mins.
‚Ä¢ Then add sugar and some water and mix well and cover and cook for 2 mins on low heat.
‚Ä¢ Then add billed milk, kesar and dryfruits chopped and cook on low heat for 5-6 mins.
‚Ä¢ At the last add cardamom pw and turn off the heat. 

‡§â‡§™‡§µ‡§æ‡§∏‡§æ‡§ö‡•á ‡§´‡§ø‡§Ç‡§ó‡§∞ ‡§ö‡§ø‡§™‡•ç‡§∏ | ‡§¨‡§ü‡§æ‡§ü‡§æ ‡§´‡•ç‡§∞‡§æ‡§á‡§ú ‡§∞‡•á‡§∏‡§ø‡§™‡•Ä | Potato Fries Recipe
‚Ä¢ ‡§Æ‡•ã‡§†‡•á ‡§≤‡§æ‡§Ç‡§¨ ‡§¨‡§ü‡§æ‡§ü‡•á 2-3 | Potatoes 2-3
‚Ä¢ ‡§∏‡•à‡§Ç‡§ß‡§µ ‡§Æ‡•Ä‡§† ‡§ö‡§µ‡•Ä‡§®‡•Å‡§∏‡§æ‡§∞ | Pink Himalayan Salt to taste
‚Ä¢ ‡§µ‡§∞‡§à ‡§™‡•Ä‡§† ¬º ‡§ï‡§™ (‡§ó‡§∞‡§ú‡•á‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§Æ‡§æ‡§£‡•á) | Sama Flour ¬º Cup 
‚Ä¢ ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡§ö‡•Ä ‡§™‡§æ‡§µ‡§°‡§∞ 1/2 tsp | Red Chilly pw ¬Ω tsp
‚Ä¢ ‡§§‡§≥‡§£‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§∏‡§æ‡§†‡•Ä ‡§§‡•á‡§≤ | Oil for frying 
Method ‚Äì
‚Ä¢ Wash and peel the potato skin, and chop like finger chips.
‚Ä¢ Wash chopped potatoes for 3-4 times and strain well
‚Ä¢ Boil some water into a pan, once water is boiling add pink Himalayan salt and potatoe pices.
‚Ä¢ Boil potatoes for 2-3 mins on high heat, take the potatoes out and drain extra water.
‚Ä¢ Spread potatoes onto a cotton cloth and wipe gently to remove excess water. And keep it into deep freezer for 15 minutes.
‚Ä¢ Then into a bowl add samal flour, salt and red chilly pw and add water to make thick slurry. 
‚Ä¢ Deep potatoes into the ready slurry and deep fry into hot oil.

Method ‚Äì 
‚Ä¢ Wash sweet potatoes well, keep it in a pressure cooker tin, put some water at the bottom of the pressure cooker, put sweet potato tin into the pressure cooker, and take 2 whistles. 
‚Ä¢ Let the pressure release from pressure cooker, take potato out and let it cool down completely. 
‚Ä¢ Once cool down, peel the skin from potato and grate the potato.
‚Ä¢ Add grated jaggery and salt to taste and mix well.
‚Ä¢ Then add sama flour to make semi soft dough, cover the dough and let it rest for 10 mintues,
‚Ä¢ After mins, take small lemon sized ball from the dough.
‚Ä¢ On rolling pad put butter paper, apply some ghee onto it , put ball onto it again put butter paper on the top of the dough and gently press the dough with the help of a plate. 
‚Ä¢ Puri is ready, deep fry puri on med to high heat.

‚Ä¢ ‡§≠‡§æ‡§ú‡§≤‡•á‡§≤‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§¶‡§æ‡§£‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§ö‡§æ ‡§ú‡§æ‡§°‡§∏‡§∞ ‡§ï‡•Ç‡§ü 3/4 ‡§ï‡§™ | Raosted peanuts crushed ¬æ cup
‚Ä¢ ‡§¶‡•Ç‡§ß 2-3 tbsp | Milk 2-3 tbsp
Method ‚Äì
‚Ä¢ Wash the sago well, keep some water into it and soak it overnight or for about 5-6 hours. (you add some milk while soaking the sago) 
‚Ä¢ Heat up some oil / ghee into a kadhai add green chilies and potatoes and some salt and saute on med heat till potatoes get nice golden brown color 
‚Ä¢ Then add sugar, roasted peanut crushed and saute for a min on low heat.
‚Ä¢ Then add soaked sago and salt to taste and saute on med heat for about 3-4 minutes, then cover and cook on low heat for 2 minutes.
‚Ä¢ After 2 minutes add milk and again stir for abut 2 minutes and again cover and cook for a min on low heat. 
‚Ä¢ After a min check again, stir for a min and serve hot. 

 ‡§®‡§æ‡§∞‡§≥‡§æ‡§ö‡•Ä ‡§ñ‡•Ä‡§∞ ‡§∞‡•á‡§∏‡§ø‡§™‡•Ä | Coconut Kheer Recipe

‚Ä¢ Heat some ghee into a kadhai and add scraped coconut and roast for 2-3 mins.
‚Ä¢ Then add sugar and some water and mix well and cover and cook for 2 mins on low heat.
‚Ä¢ Then add billed milk, kesar and dryfruits chopped and cook on low heat for 5-6 mins.
‚Ä¢ At the last add cardamom pw and turn off the heat.

‚Ä¢ Boil some water into a pan, once water is boiling add pink Himalayan salt and potatoe pices.

‚Ä¢ Deep potatoes into the ready slurry and deep fry into hot oil.

Ingredients:
Kavathachi Chutney
‚Ä¢ 2 Kavath / Wood apple
‚Ä¢ 1 cup Gudh
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Red chili powder
‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Black salt
‚Ä¢ Salt to taste
Sabudana Khichadi
‚Ä¢ 1 cup Sabudana
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Ghee
‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Cumin seed
‚Ä¢ 2~3 chopped Green chilies
‚Ä¢ 1 boiled, peeled and chopped Potato
‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup roasted Peanut powder
‚Ä¢ Salt to taste
‚Ä¢ Sugar to taste (Optional)
Ratalyacha Kis
‚Ä¢ 3~4 Ratali / Sweet potato
‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp Ghee
‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Cumin seeds
‚Ä¢ 2 chopped Green chilies
‚Ä¢ Salt to taste
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp roasted Peanut powder
Shengdanyachi Amti
‚Ä¢ 2 Green chilies
‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup roasted Peanut powder
‚Ä¢ Water
‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp Ghee
‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Cumin seeds
‚Ä¢ 1 Cinnamon stick
‚Ä¢ 2 green Cardamom
‚Ä¢ 3~4 Cloves
‚Ä¢ 3~4 Black peppercorns
‚Ä¢ Water to adjust the consistency
‚Ä¢ Salt to taste
‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp Tamarind-Gudh pulp

Method:
Kavathachi Chutney
‚Ä¢ Break open the kavath and take out the pulp. 
‚Ä¢ Add gudh and mash it well together. 
‚Ä¢ The quantity of the pulp and gudh must be same means for 1 cup pulp use 1 cup gudh. 
‚Ä¢ Add red chili powder, black salt, salt and mix it well together. Kavathachi chutney is all ready.
Sabudana Khichadi
‚Ä¢ Wash sabudana really good 3-4 times and soak it in enough water overnight or at least 4-5 
  hours. 
‚Ä¢ Heat up ghee in a pan and add cumin seeds. 
‚Ä¢ When cumin seeds splutter add green chilies and fry for few seconds. 
‚Ä¢ Add potato, soaked sabudana, roasted peanut powder, salt, sugar and mix well. 
‚Ä¢ Adding sugar is optional. You can skip it if you don‚Äôt want. 
‚Ä¢ Fry khichadi well together. 
‚Ä¢ Cover and steam on low heat for about 5-7 minutes. Sabudana khichadi is all ready.
Ratalyacha Kis
‚Ä¢ Wash the ratali well and peel them. 
‚Ä¢ Grate it into long shreds. 
‚Ä¢ Heat up ghee in a pan and add cumin seeds. 
‚Ä¢ When cumin seeds splutter add green chilies and fry well. 
‚Ä¢ Add grated ratali and fry well. 
‚Ä¢ Cover and steam for about 4-5 minutes. 
‚Ä¢ Add salt, roasted peanut powder and mix well. Ratalyacha kis is all ready. 
Shengdanyachi Amti
‚Ä¢ Blend green chilies, roasted peanut powder together well once. 
‚Ä¢ You can use 1/4 cup fresh coconut and 1/4 cup roasted peanut powder if you want. 
‚Ä¢ Add water and blend it into paste. 
‚Ä¢ Heat up ghee in a pan and add cumin seeds, cinnamon, cardamom, cloves, black 
  peppercorns. 
‚Ä¢ Fry for few seconds. Add the blended paste, water to adjust the consistency, salt, tamarind-
  gudh pulp. 
‚Ä¢ Mix well and simmer amti for about 5-6 minutes. Shengdanyachi amti is all ready.

Ingredients:
Kavathachi Chutney
‚Ä¢ 2 Kavath / Wood apple
‚Ä¢ 1 cup Gudh
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Red chili powder
‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Black salt
‚Ä¢ Salt to taste
Sabudana Khichadi
‚Ä¢ 1 cup Sabudana
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Ghee
‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Cumin seed
‚Ä¢ 2~3 chopped Green chilies
‚Ä¢ 1 boiled, peeled and chopped Potato
‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup roasted Peanut powder
‚Ä¢ Salt to taste
‚Ä¢ Sugar to taste (Optional)
Ratalyacha Kis
‚Ä¢ 3~4 Ratali / Sweet potato
‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp Ghee
‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Cumin seeds
‚Ä¢ 2 chopped Green chilies
‚Ä¢ Salt to taste
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp roasted Peanut powder
Shengdanyachi Amti
‚Ä¢ 2 Green chilies
‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup roasted Peanut powder
‚Ä¢ Water
‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp Ghee
‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Cumin seeds
‚Ä¢ 1 Cinnamon stick
‚Ä¢ 2 green Cardamom
‚Ä¢ 3~4 Cloves
‚Ä¢ 3~4 Black peppercorns
‚Ä¢ Water to adjust the consistency
‚Ä¢ Salt to taste
‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp Tamarind-Gudh pulp

Method:
Kavathachi Chutney
‚Ä¢ Break open the kavath and take out the pulp. 
‚Ä¢ Add gudh and mash it well together. 
‚Ä¢ The quantity of the pulp and gudh must be same means for 1 cup pulp use 1 cup gudh. 
‚Ä¢ Add red chili powder, black salt, salt and mix it well together. Kavathachi chutney is all ready.
Sabudana Khichadi
‚Ä¢ Wash sabudana really good 3-4 times and soak it in enough water overnight or at least 4-5 
  hours. 
‚Ä¢ Heat up ghee in a pan and add cumin seeds. 
‚Ä¢ When cumin seeds splutter add green chilies and fry for few seconds. 
‚Ä¢ Add potato, soaked sabudana, roasted peanut powder, salt, sugar and mix well. 
‚Ä¢ Adding sugar is optional. You can skip it if you don‚Äôt want. 
‚Ä¢ Fry khichadi well together. 
‚Ä¢ Cover and steam on low heat for about 5-7 minutes. Sabudana khichadi is all ready.
Ratalyacha Kis
‚Ä¢ Wash the ratali well and peel them. 
‚Ä¢ Grate it into long shreds. 
‚Ä¢ Heat up ghee in a pan and add cumin seeds. 
‚Ä¢ When cumin seeds splutter add green chilies and fry well. 
‚Ä¢ Add grated ratali and fry well. 
‚Ä¢ Cover and steam for about 4-5 minutes. 
‚Ä¢ Add salt, roasted peanut powder and mix well. Ratalyacha kis is all ready. 
Shengdanyachi Amti
‚Ä¢ Blend green chilies, roasted peanut powder together well once. 
‚Ä¢ You can use 1/4 cup fresh coconut and 1/4 cup roasted peanut powder if you want. 
‚Ä¢ Add water and blend it into paste. 
‚Ä¢ Heat up ghee in a pan and add cumin seeds, cinnamon, cardamom, cloves, black 
  peppercorns. 
‚Ä¢ Fry for few seconds. Add the blended paste, water to adjust the consistency, salt, tamarind-
  gudh pulp. 
‚Ä¢ Mix well and simmer amti for about 5-6 minutes. Shengdanyachi amti is all ready.

snippet.title: NEW! Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah - Ep 3696 - 16 Feb 2023 - Teaser
snippet.description:
Episode 3696: Prankster Ki Shart
--------------------------------------------------------
The Gokuldham residents are yet to discover the nuisance maker, and out of fear, they wander inside the clubhouse. Suddenly, Sodhi yells that he has found the mystery man, but after turning on the lights, it turns out to be Popatlal. Later, they heard someone speaking over loudspeakers. It turns out to be the mystery man who has been using these speakers to talk to everyone. He tells Gokuldham residents that he will reveal his identity if they agree to his condition. What could be his demand to the Gokuldham dwellers? Stay tuned!

Show Name ‚Äì Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah
Star Cast ‚Äì  Dilip Joshi, Disha Vakani, Amit Bhatt, Nitish Bhaluni
Episodes No - 3696, 16 Feb 2023
Produced By - Asit Kumar Modi

#TaarakMehtaKaOoltahChashmah #‡§§‡§æ‡§∞‡§ï‡§Æ‡•á‡§π‡§§‡§æ‡§ï‡§æ‡§â‡§≤‡•ç‡§ü‡§æ‡§ö‡§∂‡•ç‡§Æ‡§æ #sab 

Click here to subscribe to SAB TV:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC6-F5tO8uklgE9Zy8IvbdFw?sub_confirmation=1

Click here to subscribe to SonyLIV: 
http://www.sonyliv.com/signin

About The Show
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in Gokuldham Co-operative Society and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. Jethalal lives in Gokuldham society and owns an electronics shop.  'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Nitish Bhaluni). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises.

When he‚Äôs assigned to write a profile of megastar Celine Dion (playing herself in her first film role), he enlists her help in figuring out how to meet Mira in person‚Ä¶and win her heart. snippet.description:
Amma Mai ‡§®‡•á ‡§¶‡•Ä Thapki-Bihaan ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§ß‡§Æ‡§ï‡•Ä | Thapki Pyar Ki | ‡§•‡§™‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§™‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§∞ ‡§ï‡•Ä | Full Episode | Ep. 626

Bihaan and Thapki are shocked when Amma Mai reveals that she has kidnapped Tina. She orders them to follow all her instructions failing which Tina will be harmed. While Bani is asked to complete the kitchen chores, Bihaan comes up with a plan to find Tina. What is his plan and will it be a success? 

The bright and beautiful Thapki is pretty much perfect... except for one minor flaw - she stammers. But that doesn't hold her back. All she needs is an encouraging pat on the back,a 'thapki', which soon becomes her name. Over the course of the show, Thapki falls in love with Dhruv, but is duped into getting married to his brother, Bihaan. In spite of this cruel twist of fate, Thapki doesn't let her spirit fade and does all she can to be the ideal bahu. What does destiny hold for this charming girl with an unbeatable spirit?

snippet.title: NEW! Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah - Ep 3695 - 15 Feb 2023 - Teaser
snippet.description:
Episode 3695: Bhoot Ka Hungama
--------------------------------------------------------
The Purush Mandali members with Goli and Gogi explore the terrace for the ghost while the members of the Gokhuldham society continue to be afraid of the enigmatic figure. As they believed Iyer to be the ghost, Champaklal and Jetha with the Mahila Mandal beat him up. The Purush Mandali becomes alarmed when they cannot locate Iyer among them, believing that the ghost must have abducted him. The Gokuldham members discover a speaker in the center of the compound, which increases their terror. Stay tuned!

Show Name ‚Äì Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah
Star Cast ‚Äì  Dilip Joshi, Disha Vakani, Amit Bhatt, Nitish Bhaluni
Episodes No - 3695, 15 Feb 2023
Produced By - Asit Kumar Modi

#TaarakMehtaKaOoltahChashmah #‡§§‡§æ‡§∞‡§ï‡§Æ‡•á‡§π‡§§‡§æ‡§ï‡§æ‡§â‡§≤‡•ç‡§ü‡§æ‡§ö‡§∂‡•ç‡§Æ‡§æ #sab

https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC6-F5tO8uklgE9Zy8IvbdFw?sub_confirmation=1

Click here to subscribe to SonyLIV: 
http://www.sonyliv.com/signin

About The Show
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in Gokuldham Co-operative Society and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. Jethalal lives in Gokuldham society and owns an electronics shop.  'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Nitish Bhaluni). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises.
